e_seed/assets/problems/3025-find-the-number-of-ways-to-place-people-i/3025-t2.jpg","sequence":3,"sha256":"56d77982f1af5882a678f3a39195ec798e057b3e5bc2837d4ff1fe658abb192f","type":"image"},{"sequence":4,"text":"- The left one is the pair `(points[1], points[0])`, where `points[1]` is on the upper left side of `points[0]` and the rectangle is empty.\n\n- The middle one is the pair `(points[2], points[1])`, same as the left one it is a valid pair.\n\n- The right one is the pair `(points[2], points[0])`, where `points[2]` is on the upper left side of `points[0]`, but `points[1]` is inside the rectangle so it's not a valid pair.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\n**Input:** points = [[3,1],[1,3],[1,1]]\n\n**Output:** 2\n\n**Explanation:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3025-find-the-number-of-ways-to-place-people-i/3025-t3.jpg","sequence":5,"sha256":"eb72feb74e584363fa7a52e73e1a87d312c70ddb9d16e2c694087eee2d9428ef","type":"image"},{"sequence":6,"text":"- The left one is the pair `(points[2], points[0])`, where `points[2]` is on the upper left side of `points[0]` and there are no other points on the line they form. Note that it is a valid state when the two points form a line.\n\n- The middle one is the pair `(points[1], points[2])`, it is a valid pair same as the left one.\n\n- The right one is the pair `(points[1], points[0])`, it is not a valid pair as `points[2]` is on the border of the rectangle.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= n <= 50`\n\n- `points[i].length == 2`\n\n- `0 <= points[i][0], points[i][1] <= 50`\n\n- All `points[i]` are distinct.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Math","Geometry","Sorting","Enumeration"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a 2D array `points` of size `n x 2` representing integer coordinates of some points on a 2D plane, where `points[i] = [xi, yi]`.\n\nCount the number of pairs of points `(A, B)`, where\n\n- `A` is on the **upper left** side of `B`, and\n\n- there are no other points in the rectangle (or line) they make (**including the border**), except for the points `A` and `B`.\n\nReturn the count.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** points = [[1,1],[2,2],[3,3]]\n\n**Output:** 0\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3025-find-the-number-of-ways-to-place-people-i/3025-example1alicebob.png]]\n\nThere is no way to choose `A` and `B` such that `A` is on the upper left side of `B`.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** points = [[6,2],[4,4],[2,6]]\n\n**Output:** 2\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3025-find-the-number-of-ways-to-place-people-i/3025-t2.jpg]]\n\n- The left one is the pair `(points[1], points[0])`, where `points[1]` is on the upper left side of `points[0]` and the rectangle is empty.\n\n- The middle one is the pair `(points[2], points[1])`, same as the left one it is a valid pair.\n\n- The right one is the pair `(points[2], points[0])`, where `points[2]` is on the upper left side of `points[0]`, but `points[1]` is inside the rectangle so it's not a valid pair.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\n**Input:** points = [[3,1],[1,3],[1,1]]\n\n**Output:** 2\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3025-find-the-number-of-ways-to-place-people-i/3025-t3.jpg]]\n\n- The left one is the pair `(points[2], points[0])`, where `points[2]` is on the upper left side of `points[0]` and there are no other points on the line they form. Note that it is a valid state when the two points form a line.\n\n- The middle one is the pair `(points[1], points[2])`, it is a valid pair same as the left one.\n\n- The right one is the pair `(points[1], points[0])`, it is not a valid pair as `points[2]` is on the border of the rectangle.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= n <= 50`\n\n- `points[i].length == 2`\n\n- `0 <= points[i][0], points[i][1] <= 50`\n\n- All `points[i]` are distinct.","problemLink":"https://leetcode