 + 6 = 2`.\n\n`(0, 2, 3)`: The value of this triplet is `nums[0] - nums[2] + nums[3] = 1 - 3 + 6 = 4`.\n\nThus the answer would be `4`.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `3 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- The input is generated such that at least one triplet meets the given condition.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Ordered Set"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Given an array `nums`, return *the **maximum value** of a triplet* `(i, j, k)` *such that* `i < j < k` *and* `nums[i] < nums[j] < nums[k]`.\n\nThe **value** of a triplet `(i, j, k)` is `nums[i] - nums[j] + nums[k]`.\n\n**Example 1: **\n\n**Input: ** nums = [5,6,9]\n\n**Output: ** 8\n\n**Explanation: ** We only have one choice for an increasing triplet and that is choosing all three elements. The value of this triplet would be `5 - 6 + 9 = 8`.\n\n**Example 2: **\n\n**Input:**  nums = [1,5,3,6]\n\n**Output:**  4\n\n**Explanation: ** There are only two increasing triplets:\n\n`(0, 1, 3)`: The value of this triplet is `nums[0] - nums[1] + nums[3] = 1 - 5 + 6 = 2`.\n\n`(0, 2, 3)`: The value of this triplet is `nums[0] - nums[2] + nums[3] = 1 - 3 + 6 = 4`.\n\nThus the answer would be `4`.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `3 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- The input is generated such that at least one triplet meets the given condition.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-increasing-triplet-value/","problemName":"Maximum Increasing Triplet Value","problemNumber":3073,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given an array `nums`, return *the **maximum value** of a triplet* `(i, j, k)` *such that* `i < j < k` *and* `nums[i] < nums[j] < nums[k]`.\n\nThe **value** of a triplet `(i, j, k)` is `nums[i] - nums[j] + nums[k]`.\n\n**Exampl